Hereâs what I THINK I look like on my daily walk, VS. what I DO look likeâ¦ missing coat buttons and all! ð¤ A little reminder that not everything you see online is the reality of a situation. Here I am the most comfortably *me* and happiest in the second photo, yet to look at.. I obviously prefer the first. Weird, hey?â£
â£
Iâm currently writing about online perfection for the blog and itâs been making me think much more deeply about sharing on the internet. You seeâ¦ I prefer to create beautiful content but I prefer to consume reality. It can be tough trying to mix the two when it comes to my own work, but it is something Iâm trying to do more of all the time. I want this little space to inspire you but never make you feel like I have it all figured out - I donât want you to see anything from me and feel that you need a social media detox ð¤­ So what Iâm saying is, expect more reality but hopefully in a very âLaura wayâ. Iâm a photographer (and Iâm married to one too!) so I will always have a soft spot for a beautiful photo, but maybe the content will just be a bit more reality based going forward.
